args: No idea what you're talking about.
Who are you, stranger? Don't think I've\nseen your mug around these parts.
Name's Hawk—although you might\nbe better off calling me ＂the Reaper.＂
It's said that when you pick a target,\nthey never get out alive.
You of all people should know better\nthan to put stock in base rumors.
After all, the Bloodfist himself escaped\nthe Reaper.
If you'd come to finish the job,\nI reckon I'd be dead already.\nSo why are you here, then?
I'm trying to dismantle a rokkan criminal\norganization called the Burly Boys.
Well, that's surprising, considering\nyou used to be their leader.
...It's got nothing to do with me.\nNot anymore.
If that's how you feel, I won't push for\nyour help—but you'd be wise to keep\none ear very close to the ground.

Just advice. The Burly Boys you knew were
criminals, but at least they had a code.
This new iteration, though, is nothing
but a pack of wild jackals.
Their only business is crime, and they\ndon't care who gets hurt—including\nmembers of their own gang.
The decline is obvious, and everyone\nwho remembers their former glory\nis saying the same thing...
＂If only Gauld the Bloodfist was here.＂
I think we're done talking here, friend.\nLike I said, it's nothing to do with me.
Enough! Me and this arm have one task\nnow, and that's protecting our family.
Apologies for the trouble, in that case.\nI wish you and your family well.
Strange to see you here at this hour,\nGauld. You usually head straight home\nas soon as it's quittin' time.
You get into a fight with Angie\nor something?
I couldn't ever fight with my Angie!\nIt's just that... Well...
Still seekin' comfort in solitude, Gauld?\nHa! Some things don't ever change.
Bareed! What are you doing here?!\nAnd what more can you possibly\nwant from me at this point?
Pretty cold way to treat a man ya used\nto break bread AND necks with.
That's in the past. You and me?\nWe're done.
I used to think the same.\nTurns out it ain't quite the case.
Come with me, Gauld! Let's get out there\nand crack some skulls! I know ya gotta\nhave the same old itch I do!
That man is gone. You should know that\nbetter than any—you're the one who took\nthat fist from me.
Eh, I'm not so sure. Ya ask me,\nyou're just as strong and angry\nas ya were back in the day.
You're one of us, after all.\nYou'll always be a Burly Boy.
My place is in a small little house\nwith my small little family.
FAMILY?! You turned your back on your\nfamily! You sayin' you got someone\nelse?
A granddaughter, as a matter of fact.\nAnd I swore this arm would be used\nfor nothing but taking care of her.
Wait a sec. You ain't talkin' about\nGIRARD'S kid, are ya?!
Oh, that is RICH! You're takin' some\ngirl what ain't even yer own blood\nand callin' her yer GRANDDAUGHTER?!
Blood's got nothing to do with it.\nAngie is family. That's that.
WE were yer family, Gauld!\nUs! The Burly Boys!
Ain't no damned point in playin' house\nwith that thug's kid!
The HELL did you just say, dog?!\nYou impylin' Angie ain't my family?!
Even if me and Angie ain't\nrelated by blood, that—
N-no! That's not true!\n...Is it, Gramps?
Angie? What are you doin' here?!
Someone told me they saw you go in\nhere... But is it true, Gramps? Is all\nthe stuff that scary man said true?
True as treasure, little lass! Oh, and if\nya wanna know about yer REAL daddy,\nI can give you all the dirty details...
He was a no-good thug who ain't related\nto ol' Gauld at all.
Oh, girl. Look, it's true we're not\nrelated by blood, but—
N-no! Stay back! You're a LIAR!
Geh heh heh. Oh, this is some good info\nright here. Some good info indeed...
